14:27.913 --> 14:29.789
I would have went with
"awkward as hell",

14:29.790 --> 14:31.541
but "complicated" works.

14:31.542 --> 14:33.084
How's all that going?

14:33.085 --> 14:35.128
Oh, you know, super good,

14:34.629 --> 14:37.005
considering I just had a
child with another woman

14:37.006 --> 14:38.965
as I'm trying to patch
things up with my wife.

14:38.966 --> 14:40.383
Yes, he did.

14:40.384 --> 14:43.386
Yes, he did. Daddy did do that.

14:43.387 --> 14:44.971
Okay, thank you.

14:44.972 --> 14:47.641
Alright, apparently a tree
came down in Porter Square.

14:47.642 --> 14:49.726
Some lines are down. It's
gonna take a while to fix.

14:49.727 --> 14:51.978
Seems there's lines
down across the city.

14:51.979 --> 14:53.563
Great.

14:53.064 --> 14:54.481
Without power,

14:54.482 --> 14:57.259
that's thousands of dollars
of meat and produce gone.

14:57.260 --> 14:58.343
No, it's cool. I'll hustle the staff,

14:58.367 --> 14:59.403
we'll get everything into the walk-in.

14:59.404 --> 15:00.724
We'll empty all the ice machines,

15:00.748 --> 15:03.376
try and keep it as cool
as we can in there.

15:04.200 --> 15:06.035
Thanks, Albert.

15:06.036 --> 15:08.620
Okay, alright, kitchen staff,
let's listen up, please.

15:08.621 --> 15:10.301
I need everything
wrapped and off the line.

15:10.302 --> 15:11.782
I only want to open the freezer once.

15:11.806 --> 15:13.166
Please, if you guys could file in.

15:13.190 --> 15:14.877
I need all the ice from the bar cooler.

15:14.878 --> 15:16.628
I need ice from wherever you can get it.

15:16.629 --> 15:18.672
We got to get everything cold.

15:19.300 --> 15:20.842
A blackout?

15:20.843 --> 15:22.844
I can't believe this.

15:22.845 --> 15:24.471
You know, I...

15:24.472 --> 15:26.139
gave Neil's money away.

15:26.140 --> 15:28.308
I finally let go of Andrew,

15:28.309 --> 15:30.477
took a loan out on my home,

15:30.478 --> 15:33.521
and now this?

15:33.522 --> 15:34.522
You're not alone.

15:34.523 --> 15:36.399
What are you trying to tell me?

15:36.400 --> 15:39.110
If this isn't a sign from God...

15:39.111 --> 15:41.446
This is a sign. This is Him
trying to tell me something.

15:41.447 --> 15:43.698
Oh, Gina, this isn't
just happening to you.

15:44.950 --> 15:47.243
Alright, it's happening to
both of us. I'm your partner.

15:47.244 --> 15:49.537
- Yeah, I know that, D.
- Do you?

15:48.538 --> 15:50.623
'Cause you're not acting like it.

15:50.624 --> 15:52.750
I'm here for you, and I need this.

15:52.751 --> 15:54.919
I need this just as much as you do.

16:02.969 --> 16:04.762
Um, sorry.

16:04.763 --> 16:06.222
We're closed.

16:06.223 --> 16:08.432
Oh. It's really coming down out there.

16:08.433 --> 16:10.309
Think I can dry off for a few?

16:10.310 --> 16:11.977
Sure.

16:11.978 --> 16:13.562
Thank you.

16:19.945 --> 16:22.863
Hey, you hungry?

16:22.864 --> 16:24.448
I mean, I could eat.

16:24.449 --> 16:26.117
Cool.

16:26.118 --> 16:28.202
Have a seat.

16:45.221 --> 16:47.473
Damn it, Maggie.

16:56.816 --> 16:58.901
Maggie!

16:58.902 --> 17:01.195
Get in!

17:01.196 --> 17:04.156
It's pouring.

17:05.492 --> 17:07.076
Please.

17:17.253 --> 17:19.088
Hey, leave out a few of those clams.

17:19.089 --> 17:20.839
Yes, Chef.

17:20.340 --> 17:22.622
And grab me some Pinot Gris
from the bar when you're done.

17:22.646 --> 17:25.397
Right away.

17:29.892 --> 17:32.102
You gonna let me in on whatever this is?

17:32.103 --> 17:35.523
This is me hearing my partner.

17:36.565 --> 17:38.984
Did I ever tell you about my first job?

17:38.985 --> 17:41.319
It's actually where Albert and I met.

17:40.820 --> 17:43.947
It was this little Italian
restaurant in Somerville.

17:43.948 --> 17:45.532
I was 16.

17:45.533 --> 17:47.701
Started off as a dishwasher.

17:47.702 --> 17:50.329
I'd help the cooks with
whatever they needed...

17:50.330 --> 17:53.707
uh, peeling potatoes, chopping onions.

17:53.708 --> 17:56.752
I'd come in early, stay late, and...

17:57.338 --> 17:58.505
You know what?

17:58.506 --> 18:01.174
I think I just wanted to
get out of the house...

18:01.175 --> 18:03.718
after everything that happened.

18:03.719 --> 18:05.136
Mm.

18:05.137 --> 18:07.013
So, every day before our shift,

18:07.014 --> 18:08.556
we'd have a family meal.

18:08.557 --> 18:10.433
They'd cook this massive feast

18:10.434 --> 18:13.144
from whatever was left
over from the day before,

18:13.145 --> 18:15.688
and we'd... we'd drag
these tables together.

18:15.689 --> 18:17.732
They'd...

18:17.233 --> 18:20.193
They would make this
horrible screeching sound.

18:21.696 --> 18:23.363
But to me, that sound was everything

18:23.364 --> 18:25.782
because for 25 minutes, every day,

18:25.783 --> 18:28.535
this random group of misfits and nomads

18:28.536 --> 18:30.996
would sit together and share a meal.

18:30.997 --> 18:34.708
For that 25 minutes,
they were my family.

18:36.210 --> 18:38.045
Hmm.

18:38.046 --> 18:40.297
From your buddy up front.

18:40.298 --> 18:42.818
If you're gonna cook in the dark,
you might as well do it right.

18:42.842 --> 18:43.967
Alright.

18:43.968 --> 18:45.552
What is that?

18:45.553 --> 18:46.762
Hey.

18:46.763 --> 18:47.763
Whoo!

18:47.764 --> 18:49.765
- Hey, she's back.
- Mm-hmm.

18:51.309 --> 18:52.893
What?

18:52.394 --> 18:55.312
Oh, if I could, I'd take back

18:55.313 --> 18:57.147
all the harm I caused this past year,

18:57.148 --> 18:59.775
but not you, Charlotte.

18:59.776 --> 19:01.610
Mnh-mnh.

19:01.611 --> 19:05.197
You are the one good
thing to come out of it.

19:07.784 --> 19:09.827
VoilÃƒÂ .

19:09.828 --> 19:11.620
Wow.

19:11.621 --> 19:14.832
You know, I would've
settled for just a sandwich.

19:14.333 --> 19:16.292
Hmm. I wouldn't have.

19:17.528 --> 19:19.570
You know, call your crew.

19:19.071 --> 19:21.281
- There's more where that came from.
- Oh.

19:21.282 --> 19:23.658
Well, in that case,
you'll still need this.

19:23.659 --> 19:24.993
Thank you.

19:26.538 --> 19:27.978
- Gary.
- Have you seen Maggie?

19:28.002 --> 19:30.124
I thought she might come
here to talk to you.

19:30.125 --> 19:31.792
No. Why? Is everything okay?

19:31.793 --> 19:34.044
No.

19:35.296 --> 19:37.297
Oh, welcome back, stranger.

19:37.298 --> 19:38.298
Quick update...

19:38.299 --> 19:40.426
we filed an extension
on the Madigan case,

19:40.427 --> 19:43.178
I lost eight pounds, uh,
the new temp is super cute,

19:43.179 --> 19:44.680
but straight... for now...

19:44.681 --> 19:46.433
and did I mention I lost eight pounds?

19:47.475 --> 19:49.727
Yeah, you lost eight
pounds. That's great.

19:49.228 --> 19:51.521
But I gained five of them back
from the stress of it all.

19:51.522 --> 19:52.939
I was worried about you.

19:52.940 --> 19:55.024
Where have you been?

19:56.360 --> 19:59.696
Woman, please, when have
you ever not confided in me?

20:00.823 --> 20:02.699
- Come on.
- This should be good.

20:02.700 --> 20:04.034
...Only to discover

20:04.035 --> 20:06.536
that she didn't even take her phone.

20:06.537 --> 20:08.038
So, I have no idea where she is,

20:08.039 --> 20:09.372
no way to get ahold of her,

20:09.373 --> 20:11.013
even if she did want
to talk to me, and...

20:11.037 --> 20:12.237
Whoop.

20:13.044 --> 20:15.336
Patricia keeps texting her.

20:15.337 --> 20:18.048
It's not gonna happen, Trish.

20:17.549 --> 20:19.633
I just don't understand

20:19.634 --> 20:23.262
how she could do all of
this to her own daughter.

20:23.263 --> 20:25.682
I can.

20:28.226 --> 20:31.311
That's exactly what I'm
doing to Sophie and Danny.

20:31.312 --> 20:32.437
Um...

20:32.438 --> 20:35.065
unless you've secretly
harvested Danny's organs,

20:35.066 --> 20:36.191
I don't think it is.

20:36.192 --> 20:38.026
Alright, look, I'll tell you this...

20:37.527 --> 20:39.528
as a mom, the moment your kids are born,

20:39.529 --> 20:41.405
you're just hard-wired to protect them.

20:41.406 --> 20:42.656
Not my mother.

20:42.657 --> 20:44.950
She never protected anything,
except maybe her SAG card.

20:46.119 --> 20:47.912
I'm not saying that
what she did is right,

20:47.913 --> 20:50.456
I just understand how in that moment...

20:50.457 --> 20:52.875
she just didn't want Maggie to know

20:52.876 --> 20:54.919
her brother had suffered.

20:59.675 --> 21:00.884
You know, uh...

21:00.885 --> 21:03.595
you... you have to know
the last thing I wanted

21:03.596 --> 21:05.639
was to come between you and your family.

21:06.682 --> 21:09.518
Well, if it makes you feel any better,

21:09.519 --> 21:11.834
we have been dysfunctional
for quite some time.

21:11.859 --> 21:13.005
Oh, good.

21:20.321 --> 21:25.117
After Chad died, um...

21:25.118 --> 21:27.994
we were never really the same.

21:27.995 --> 21:32.207
My mom, she was, um...

21:32.208 --> 21:33.667
she was stuck.

21:33.668 --> 21:37.379
She... kept his room exactly how it was,

21:37.380 --> 21:39.714
like a shrine...

21:39.215 --> 21:43.344
and she just kind of walled
herself off from everyone...

21:43.345 --> 21:45.095
including me.

21:48.350 --> 21:50.351
Especially me.

21:58.194 --> 22:00.278
Uh, Gary, wh... what are you doing here?

22:00.279 --> 22:02.072
Well, I got your message.

22:02.073 --> 22:05.200
Uh... Technically, Maggie's message.

22:06.285 --> 22:08.244
So, she hasn't seen any of my texts?

22:08.245 --> 22:10.330
- No.
- Oh.

22:10.331 --> 22:12.707
Come in, come in.

22:14.794 --> 22:16.836
It's probably for the best.

22:16.837 --> 22:19.547
I don't think she wants to talk to you.

22:19.548 --> 22:21.049
Or me, or...

22:21.050 --> 22:23.176
anyone, for that matter.

22:23.177 --> 22:25.095
Not for nothing.

22:25.096 --> 22:27.514
She kind of got a bomb dropped on her

22:27.015 --> 22:29.058
over bagels, so...

22:30.268 --> 22:32.144
- ...there's that.
- Oh.

22:32.145 --> 22:34.355
What have I done?

22:35.899 --> 22:38.025
I mean...

22:38.026 --> 22:43.030
everybody hates me...
my husband, my daughter.

22:43.031 --> 22:45.825
Now... Eric.

22:53.375 --> 22:55.710
Patricia...

22:55.711 --> 22:59.547
what you and Eugene went through...

22:59.548 --> 23:03.342
losing a child...

23:02.843 --> 23:05.304
I cannot imagine.

23:07.806 --> 23:11.017
I do get that it brings you comfort

23:11.018 --> 23:15.772
knowing that some part
of Chad is still alive.

23:17.274 --> 23:19.734
But your husband...

23:21.237 --> 23:24.739
...he's not wrong.

23:24.740 --> 23:27.659
Eric is not your son,

23:27.660 --> 23:31.663
and all of this...

23:31.664 --> 23:35.625
him...

23:35.626 --> 23:37.835
is it really worth losing your family?

23:40.339 --> 23:43.074
What if it's too late?

23:44.135 --> 23:47.136
Well, there's only one way to find out.

23:47.137 --> 23:49.347
Pick up the phone, Patricia.

23:49.348 --> 23:52.267
You just said Maggie
doesn't want to talk to me.

23:52.268 --> 23:55.979
That is not who you need to call.

24:02.260 --> 24:04.466
I don't get it. She's dry,
she's fed, she's burped.

24:04.566 --> 24:06.733
Could be an ear infection.
What? That's a thing, right?

24:06.734 --> 24:08.760
Ear infection? Yes, that's a thing,
but she's not touching her ears.

24:08.761 --> 24:10.161
We're the worst babysitters ever.

24:10.162 --> 24:11.997
I am not her babysitter.

24:11.498 --> 24:13.540
No, no, no. Ed, I didn't mean it like...

24:13.541 --> 24:15.822
No, I should know how to calm
her down. She's my daughter.

24:15.846 --> 24:17.406
I should know all of her little quirks.

24:17.407 --> 24:19.047
I should know which
cry means she's hungry

24:19.048 --> 24:20.895
and which cry means
she's tired, but I don't.

24:22.884 --> 24:24.510
I don't want to be her babysitter.

24:24.511 --> 24:25.844
I want to be her father.

24:25.845 --> 24:27.221
It's okay. Shh.

24:28.598 --> 24:31.850
She's congested.

24:31.851 --> 24:34.102
I know what to do.

24:34.103 --> 24:36.438
Okay, okay, sweetie.
It's gonna be okay. Shh.

24:35.939 --> 24:37.732
So, everyone knows?

24:37.733 --> 24:40.026
Not Theo or any of the kids.

24:40.027 --> 24:42.147
Why didn't you call me and
tell me what was happening?

24:42.171 --> 24:43.738
I could have been there for you.

24:43.739 --> 24:45.948
Honestly, I couldn't face anyone.

24:45.949 --> 24:48.200
Well, what are you doing?

24:48.201 --> 24:51.912
I'm trying to make it work.

24:51.913 --> 24:53.706
Uh-huh.

24:53.707 --> 24:55.207
What?

24:54.708 --> 24:56.793
- Nothing.
- Go on. Tell me.

24:56.794 --> 24:58.169
I want to know what you think.

24:58.170 --> 24:59.212
But do you?

24:59.213 --> 25:00.797
Why do you always make me work for it?

25:00.798 --> 25:03.049
Okay. Here goes. Uh...

25:02.550 --> 25:05.302
I'd understand if you never
want to see Eddie again,

25:05.303 --> 25:07.846
and I'd understand if you took him back.

25:07.847 --> 25:09.014
He's your husband,

25:09.015 --> 25:10.515
and you have a child together.

25:10.516 --> 25:12.309
What I can't understand

25:12.310 --> 25:14.603
is trying to make it work.

25:14.604 --> 25:16.855
You either make this work or you don't.

25:16.356 --> 25:19.108
Katherine Saville
doesn't try to win cases.

25:19.109 --> 25:20.568
She wins them.

25:20.569 --> 25:24.822
If you're going to be in, be all in.

25:25.824 --> 25:27.825
Thanks, Carter.

25:27.826 --> 25:31.162
So, is this a bad time to tell you

25:31.163 --> 25:33.164
that we need Baby Mama's signature

25:33.165 --> 25:35.416
